 If you can’t explain something in simple terms, you don’t understand it 

 
 posted by  Jason Kottke     Jun 15, 2017 
 


 

 

 In the early 1960s, Richard Feynman gave a series of undergraduate lectures that were collected into a book called  the Feynman Lectures on Physics . Absent from the book was  a lecture  Feynman gave on planetary motion, but a later finding of the notes enabled David Goodstein, a colleague of Feynman’s, to write a book about it:  Feynman’s Lost Lecture . From an excerpt of the book published in  a 1996 issue of Caltech’s Engineering &amp; Science magazine : 

 Feynman was a truly great teacher. He prided himself on being able to devise ways to explain even the most profound ideas to beginning students. Once, I said to hi